      • quicksort

        public ArrayBasedList<java.lang.String> quicksort(ArrayBasedList<java.lang.String> arr,
                                                  int floor,
                                                  int ceiling)
        Non-recursive quicksorting algorithm. Implemented referencing pseudocode from http://csg.sph.umich.edu/abecasis/class/2008/615.07.pdf
        Parameters:
        arr - The ArrayBasedList to perform the sort on.
        floor - The lower boundary of the sort.
        ceiling - The higher boundary of the sory.
        Returns:
        arr The sorted version of the ArrayBasedList initially passed in.

      • partition

        public int partition(ArrayBasedList<java.lang.String> arr,
                     int start,
                     int stop)
        Creates the partition around the pivot point in the quicksort, narrowing down the current set of data.
        Parameters:
        arr - The ArrayBasedList the quicksort is being performed on.
        start - The start of the partition.
        stop - Where the partition stops.
        Returns:
        up Moving an object up through the ArrayBasedList.
